FBIS3-10006 "drlat040_a_94005" FBIS-LAT-94-040 Document Type:Daily Report 1 March 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Cigarette Industry Stabilizing, Meeting Demand FL0103004194 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 GMT 28 Feb 94 FL0103004194 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Adolfo Diaz, vice president of the Council of Ministers, said that the productive results achieved by the cigarette industry is leading it toward stabilization since the factories are close to reaching the expected levels for 1994, aimed at satisfying the national demand for the product. In an extensive communique printed in the TRABAJADORES newspaper, Diaz referred to the increased number of smokers among the Cuban population and stressed that the stable production and sale of cigarettes not only satisfies the consumers' needs, but represents a considerable contribution to the national economy, which is suffering the consequences of excess currency. Adolfo Diaz was hesitant to predict when the sale of cigarettes would be released, considering the many factors that would make such a prediction inaccurate.
